\lim_{n\to\infty} \int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} \Big|\sin((2n+1)x)\Big| f(x) dx = \frac{2}{\pi}\int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} f(x) dx
\frac{1}{\sin x} - \frac{1}{x}
\lim_{n\to\infty} \int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} \Big|\sin((2n+1)x)\Big| \Big(\frac{1}{\sin x} - \frac{1}{x} \Big) dx = \frac{2}{\pi} \int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} \Big(\frac{1}{\sin x} - \frac{1}{x} \Big) dx\\ = \frac{2}{\pi} \left[\log\left(\frac{\tan(\frac{x}{2})}{x}\right)\right]_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} = \frac{2}{\pi} \left[\log\frac{2}{\pi} - \log{\frac12}\right] = \frac{2}{\pi} \log\frac{4}{\pi} \tag{*1}
\int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}}  \frac{|\sin((2n+1)x)|}{x} dx = \int_0^{\pi(n+\frac12)} \frac{|\sin x|}{x} dx = \int_0^{\pi n} \frac{|\sin x|}{x} dx + O(\frac{1}{n}) 
